The start of the week will see most parts of the country experiencing a fine to warm day, according to data from the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region It will be fine and cool in Gauteng. The expected UVB sunburn index will be high. Mpumalanga will be fine and cool. It will be fine and warm in Limpopo. It will be fine and cool in the North West and the Free State. It will be fine to warm, with morning frost in places over the interior of the Northern Cape. The wind along the coast will be moderate to fresh south-easterly. The Western Cape will be fine and cool. Morning frost is expected in places over the interior and there will be fog patches along the south-west and south coast. It will be warm over the West Coast District interior.The wind along the coast will be moderate westerly to north-westerly, but south-easterly to southerly north of Cape Columbine.The expected UVB sunburn index is low. The Eastern Cape is expected to be fine. It will be cool to warm along the coast. The wind along the coast will be light becoming south westerly. It will be fine and cool but warm in the north-east parts of the KwaZulu-Natal. The wind along the coast will be Moderate to fresh easterly to north-easterly. The expected UVB sunburn index is moderate.  Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days